<title>USA: Universal Outdoor issues $200 mln notes.</title>
<headline>Universal Outdoor issues $200 mln notes.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-10-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following high-yield debt issue from Universal Outdoor Holdings Inc was priced on Friday, according to lead manager Bear Stearns &amp; Co.</p>
<p>Universal Outdoor said proceeds will be used to repay bank debt, repurchase certain outstanding notes and finance a portion of the purchase price in connection with certain acquisitions.</p>
<p>BORROWER UNIVERSAL OUTDOOR HOLDINGS INC</p>
<p>AMT $200 MLN	   COUPON 9.75 PCT   MATURITY 10/15/06</p>
<p>TYPE SNR SUB NOTES   ISS PRICE 99.372  FIRST PAY DATE 4/15/97</p>
<p>LAST MOODY B1	  YIELD 9.85 PCT    PAY FREQ SEMI-ANNUAL</p>
<p>LAST S&amp;P B-MINUS     SPREAD 325 BP     CALLABLE NON-CALL FIVE</p>
<p>NOTES THREE YEAR EQUITY CALL FOR $70 MLN AT 110.</p>
<p>-- U.S. corporate bond unit, 212 859-1672</p>
